      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Strategically, relying solely on a traditionally European cast risks alienating the rapidly expanding global consumer base driving modern wealth. The shift is moving away from purely ancestral representation toward universal symbols of modern success. A more powerful approach is casting diverse, impeccably tailored individuals who embody global authority—making the *context* of the wear and the *achievement* the primary visual language, not just racial representation.",
      "source": "target",
